<subSubSection pageId="112" pageNumber="113" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="112.[151,1437,1410,2011]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1734,1759]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Etymology</emphasis>
. The genus name is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerken" authorityYear="2018" box="[576,755,1734,1759]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Phallolamprops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[576,755,1734,1759]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Phallolamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the combination of the similar genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Sars. Gender" authorityYear="1863" box="[1272,1385,1735,1758]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Lamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1272,1385,1735,1758]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Lamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[151,234,1770,1795]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">phallus</emphasis>
, in reference to the penial lobes. Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="113" lastPageNumber="114" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="112.[151,1437,1410,2011]" lastBlockId="113.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="113" lastPageNumber="114" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1806,1831]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Remarks.</emphasis>
This genus is quite similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerken" authorityYear="2018" box="[651,879,1806,1831]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Phallolampropoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[651,879,1806,1831]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Phallolampropoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be differentiated by the long antenna and the ventral elaboration on pleonites 
<quantity box="[590,669,1842,1867]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.81" metricValueMax="5.08" metricValueMin="2.54" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" unit="in" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 in</quantity>
the adult male. If only females are present, the genus can be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Normani Bonnier" authorityYear="1896" box="[380,546,1878,1903]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Hemilamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[380,546,1878,1903]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Hemilamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by pereopod 1, and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Sars. Gender" authorityYear="1863" box="[865,978,1879,1902]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Lamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[865,978,1879,1902]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Lamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by article 1 of the uropod exopod. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Normani Bonnier" authorityYear="1896" box="[151,316,1914,1939]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Hemilamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,316,1914,1939]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Hemilamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, pereopod 1 has the basis shorter than the rest of the articles together, while in the new genus pereopod 1 has the basis longer than all other articles together. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Sars. Gender" authorityYear="1863" box="[924,1037,1951,1974]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Lamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[924,1037,1951,1974]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Lamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, article 1 of the uropod exopod is usually less than 0.5 the length of article 2, while in the new genus, article 1 of the uropod exopod is much greater than 0.5 the length of article 2. Unfortunately, without adult males, there is no way to differentiate between the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerken" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,331,188,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Phallolamprops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,331,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Phallolamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerken" authorityYear="2018" box="[385,613,188,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Phallolampropoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[385,613,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Phallolampropoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except by differentiating among the different species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
